45         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
46         | PURPOSE
47         | Creates a variable-level information report for all datasets in a
48         | designated directory. For each dataset the report lists variable
49         | number, name, type, length, position, and label. Results are exported to a
50         | multi-sheet Excel workbook (.xlsx) in the DAC_Documents subfolder
51         | of the output directory, with one sheet per dataset.
52         | Output columns: NUM, VARIABLE, TYPE, LEN, POS, LABEL.
53         |
54         | 1.0: REQUIRED SYSPARM PARAMETERS (pipe-delimited)
55         | INPUT_DIRECTORY  = Path to the folder containing SAS datasets
56         |                    (.sas7bdat) to be summarized
57         | OUTPUT_DIRECTORY = Path to the folder where the DAC_Documents
58         |                    subfolder and output file will be created.
59         |                    Must exist prior to execution.
60         |
61         | 2.0: OPTIONAL PARAMETERS
62         | None. All parameters are supplied via SYSPARM.
63         |
64         | USAGE:
65         |   sas -sysparm "input_directory|output_directory"
66         |       -sysin variable_info_cli20260320.sas
67         |
68         | OUTPUT STRUCTURE:
69         |   output_directory\
70         |   └── DAC_Documents\
71         |       └── variable_info_<GGG_PARENT>_<GG_PARENT>_<G_PARENT>_<YYYYMMDD>.xlsx
72         |           (one Excel sheet per dataset)
73         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
74         | OPERATING SYSTEM COMPATIBILITY
75         | SAS v9.4 or Higher: Yes
76         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
77         | MACRO CALL
78         |
79         | Not applicable. Script is invoked directly via the SAS command
80         | line using -sysin and -sysparm.
81         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
82         | EXAMPLES
83         |
84         | Basic usage:
85         |   sas -sysparm "C:\data\input|C:\data\output"
86         |       -sysin variable_info_cli20260320.sas
3                                           The SAS System                  15:33 Monday, May 18, 2026

87         |
88         | Using a study-specific directory:
89         |   sas -sysparm "C:\studies\trial1\sas|C:\studies\trial1\output"
90         |       -sysin variable_info_cli20260320.sas
91         *------------------------------------------------------------------*/
